"Xintiandi feels extremely guilty about this, thanks the government for its efforts in combating the epidemic and asks the government for its forgiveness. Xintiandi will actively cooperate with the government and provide human and material assistance within its capacity. "

Almost two weeks after the first confirmed case of new crown pneumonia was reported at the new world church in Taegu, New World Church President Lee Man-Hee finally appeared to plead guilty. As of midnight on March 2, there were over 4,000 confirmed cases of NCP in South Korea, nearly 60% of which were related to the new World Church in Taegu.

According to Yonhap News Agency reported that 2 pm local time, Lee Man-Hee held a news conference on the new pneumonia epidemic. It was the first time Lee Man-Hee had spoken out publicly since the outbreak of the disease in South Korea.

At a news conference, Lee Man-Hee, 88, knelt to apologize. He said that although not the intention, but so many infected people, his no face, sincerely apologize to the people, and promised to fully cooperate with the government to prevent and control the epidemic. Lee Man-Hee said the church had now refrained from holding any meetings and had closed all venues.

At the press conference, demonstrators at the scene shouted that Lee Man-Hee was responsible for the outbreak at the new world church in Taegu. The news conference lasted about 20 minutes and 200 police officers were on hand to keep order, Yonhap said.

As of midnight Tuesday, 2,418 of the 4,212 confirmed cases of NCP in South Korea were related to the new World Church in Taegu, accounting for 57.4% and the case fatality rate was 0.5% , including 1,235 cases aged between 20 and 29 years, may Be influenced by the younger female followers of Xintiandi. In addition, the new World Taegu church-related confirmed cases are not only in Daegu city, but in 14 provinces and cities across the country.

According to public information, the new World Church, full name "New World Jesus Proof Tabernacle Temple" , was established by Lee Man-Hee on March 14,1984, and is headquartered in Gocheon city, Gyeonggi Province, South Korea. Currently, South Korea has started to detect the virus in about 310,000 believers of the new world church, the church-related cases are expected to continue to climb.

According to South Korea's "joongang Ilbo" reported on the 2nd, the South Korean government said that immigration records show that some members of the new heaven and Earth Church had visited Wuhan in January this year, the exact number has not been determined. However, Quan Junxu, Deputy Minister of the Central Epidemic Prevention Department, said the number of Xintiandi believers travelling to and from Wuhan is not large, and the relationship with the epidemic needs to be further investigated.

At a press conference on the 2nd, South Korea's head of the Central Epidemic Prevention Headquarters, Jeong eun-kyung, said that a preliminary investigation had been conducted into the entry and exit records of believers returning from China to Xintiandi. One or two people were involved, one of whom returned from Wuhan on January 8, but the devotee was not listed as a churchgoer and no infection was confirmed.

According to Yonhap News Agency, the South Korean Ministry of Justice released records show that from July last year to February 27 this year, a total of 42"new world" believers from Wuhan into South Korea, the South Korean side is investigating the 42 people.

On February 18, a 61-year-old Korean woman became the 31st confirmed case of pneumonia in South Korea and the first confirmed case of the new World Church in Taegu. He attended church with 1,001 worshippers on February 9 and 16. Since then, the number of confirmed cases has increased rapidly in Daegu city, with a 31st patient-centered cluster of infections.

On March 1, the Seoul Metropolitan Government charged Lee Man-Hee and 12 branch leaders of Shintiandi with violating the Infectious Disease Prevention Act, as well as killing and wounding, to the District Public Prosecutors Office in Seoul, the main suspect is "no active measures to prevent the spread of the epidemic. ".

On the same day, Seoul Mayor Park Won-soon posted an article on his facebook account titled "As the core person responsible for this incident, please come forward to solve the problem immediately, " urging members of the new World Church to apologize to the nation, ask Lee Man-Hee himself and all the members of the new heaven and Earth Church to be tested and actively cooperate with the epidemic prevention. The Daegu city government also took legal action against Xintiandi Church on the grounds of providing false information and obstructing the government's epidemic prevention work.

Another victims'group, Xintiandi, announced on February 27 that it had embezzled and embezzled assets in violation of the Infectious Disease Prevention Act and the special economic crimes aggravated Punishment Act, according to South Korea's joongang Ilbo, the indictment against Lee Man-Hee was released to the press in a 374 page indictment.

According to the complaint, there were 429 discrepancies between the 1,100 meeting places published by the New World Church and the list of properties owned by the Church as reported in the annual general meeting. In addition, some patients know that diagnosis was found to be a new heaven and earth believers, but the church tried to hide the identity of believers, and even instigated believers to lie. "It is more important not to reveal your identity, " rather than prevent and control the outbreak, they said.

The church submitted the list of believers, did not include more than 70,000"most likely to be infected with the virus" of the list of prospective members and important people in the church list. When the government asked the church to provide a list of prospective church members on the 27th, Xintiandi was refused on the grounds that "the prospective members of the church are not full members and can not provide a list" .

In response, in an interview with the CNN on the 1st, Kim shin-chang, the head of the international mission of the New World Church, denied that the new World Church was responsible for the recent surge in the number of infected people in South Korea, saying that the authorities were trying to "exaggerate" the church's involvement, to pass the buck to the government.

He apologised for the "concern for the Korean people" about the church, but said it had been fully co-operating with the government and transparent despite its shortcomings. He acknowledged that the church encourages people to deny their identity, but said it was not a cover-up but because Xintiandi was seen in some areas as "heretical" and its followers were discriminated against.

The way in which Xintiandi worships has long been questioned. Kim du-yeon, a former Xintiandi devotee, told CNN in February that the church had never justified his absence from church events by citing illness. At Church, the Faithful "huddle together like Sardines as food" and are not allowed to wear masks to avoid "disrespect to God" .

Jin counters that these claims are outdated and inaccurate, and that symptomatic believers have been required to either not enter places of worship or to wear masks since January.

"We closed all our offices to prevent further spread. Our management process has been delayed because all members work from home and are self-segregated to the maximum extent possible, " Jin said. "I'm sure there are places where we can do better, but we want to stress that we have done our best in this situation. "

The Catholic archdiocese of Taegu in South Korea first stopped mass after a spate of confirmed cases on February 19, followed by 16 parishes within a week. This is the first time in the 236-year history of the Korean Catholic Church. In addition, South Korea's Buddhist community has suspended all Dharma meetings, and most Christian churches have changed Sunday services to online services.

Lee Man-Hee, president of the New World Church, on February 21st urged worshippers to "follow the instructions of the government" by cutting back on meetings and converting to online sermons. He said on March 2 that he had been tested negative for the new coronavirus after being quarantined at his home in Gyeonggi Province.

"The epidemic is first and foremost a large-scale disaster, not just a personal problem. It is not just our own efforts, but the government's efforts to prevent the spread of the epidemic, " Lee Man-Hee said at a press conference on Tuesday. "Now is not the time to find out who is right and who is wrong. Let the universe take care of you. "
